Super Eagles striker, Victor Osimhen, has lost his father. Osimhen took to his Twitter page on Sunday to announce the passing of his father while sharing a write-up that had “R.I.P. Dad” He said: “R.I.P. Dad. No words to describe this feeling.” Osimhen currently plays for French Ligue 1 side, Lille. The 21-year-old has drawn the interest of Tottenham Hotspur, Liverpool, Chelsea and Manchester United in the past. His current contract with Lille will expire at the end of the 2023/2024 season. Osimhen is expected to cost around £70 million. Transfer: Real Madrid set to sign Victor Osimhen Mourinho set to bring Victor Osimhen to Tottenham Rohr hints at new position for Osimhen in Super Eagles team